s%3A%2F%2Fwww.jchs.harvard.edu%2Fhousing-americas-older-adults-2023%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20report%20last%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%20finding%20that%20the%20US%20didn't%20have%20anywhere%20near%20enough%20housing%20and%20care%20services%20for%20boomers%20as%20they%20age.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHomeowners%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.curbed.com%2Farticle%2Fnimbys-veto-power-norman-mailer-power-neighborhoods.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoppose%20new%20and%20denser%20housing%20in%20their%20neighborhoods%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20a%20major%20reason%20so%20many%20American%20communities%20are%20short%20on%20homes.%20Those%20who%20oppose%20building%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsites.bu.edu%2Fkleinstein%2Ffiles%2F2017%2F09%2FEinsteinPalmerGlick_ZoningPartic.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edisproportionately%20older%20homeowners%3C%2Fa%3E.%20While%20boomers%20didn't%20create%20many%20of%20these%20not-in-my-backyard%20laws%20that%20restrict%20housing%20construction%2C%20in%20many%20cases%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2018-11-05%2Fhow-boomer-homeowners-blocked-affordable-housing%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethey've%20protected%20such%20regulations%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20dominating%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cambridge.org%2Fcore%2Fjournals%2Fperspectives-on-politics%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fwho-participates-in-local-government-evidence-from-meeting-minutes%2FC6505940E607B6392C4A8F53A9363DB1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eattendance%20at%20community%20board%20meetings%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20fighting%20housing%20projects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f15e3f7a-80ee-41f4-a75b-1e6b9d8b5adb%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBoomers%20are%20struggling%20to%20find%20accessible%2C%20affordable%20homes%20amid%20rising%20costs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20people%20age%2C%20they%20tend%20to%20need%20more%20accessible%20homes%20with%20fewer%20stairs%20and%20wider%20hallways.%20As%20they%20stop%20driving%2C%20many%20also%20want%20to%20live%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Farticles%2FPMC7793713%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20walkable%20or%20transit-friendly%20places%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20access%20amenities%20and%20combat%20isolation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20restrictive%20land-use%20laws%2C%20including%20those%20prohibiting%20apartment%20buildings%20in%20areas%20with%20single-family%20homes%2C%20have%20made%20accessible%20housing%20options%20harder%20to%20find%20in%20many%20of%20the%20communities%20boomers%20have%20called%20home%20for%20decades.%20Less%20than%204%25%20of%20US%20homes%20have%20the%20three%20essential%20factors%20necessary%20for%20those%20with%20limited%20mobility%3A%20a%20single%20floor%2C%20wide%20hallways%20and%20doorways%2C%20and%20no%20steps%20to%20get%20in%2C%20the%20Harvard%20report%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20just%20such%20a%20diversity%20of%20households%20that%20we're%20not%20really%20serving%20with%20the%20traditional%20single-family%20house%2C%26quot%3B%20Molinsky%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20older%20homeowners%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0particularly%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usatoday.com%2Fstory%2Fmoney%2F2024%2F07%2F24%2Fhome-ownership-retirement-bad-idea%2F74498345007%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egrowing%20number%20who%20still%20have%20mortgages%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0are%20struggling%20with%20rising%20insurance%20premiums.%20Nationally%2C%20home-insurance%20premiums%20rose%20by%20an%20average%20of%2021%25%20from%20May%202022%20to%20May%202023%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.policygenius.com%2Fhomeowners-insurance%2Fhome-insurance-pricing-report-2023%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DHomeowners%2520insurance%2520premiums%2520in%2520the%2Cactive%2520policies%2520quoted%2520for%2520renewal.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EPolicygenius%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20insurance%20marketplace%2C%20found.%20Insurance%20companies%20are%20increasingly%20dropping%20customers%20and%20pulling%20out%20of%20entire%20regions%2C%20particularly%20those%20hardest%20hit%20by%20climate-related%20disasters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Harvard%20report%20noted%20that%20places%20retirees%20had%20flocked%20to%20in%20recent%20decades%20like%20South%20Florida%20and%20Arizona%20also%20face%20some%20of%20the%20most%20severe%20climate-related%20impacts%2C%20including%20regular%20flooding%2C%20fires%2C%20and%20extreme%20heat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20record%20number%20of%20homeowners%2065%20and%20older%20are%20cost-burdened%2C%20meaning%20they%20spend%20more%20than%2030%25%20of%20their%20income%20on%20housing%20and%20utilities%2C%20the%20report%20found.%20This%20is%20particularly%20difficult%20for%20those%20on%20fixed%20incomes.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20older%20people%20are%20increasingly%20facing%20homelessness.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.governing.com%2Furban%2Fthe-nations-homeless-population-is-aging-dramatically%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ESingle%20adults%2050%20or%20older%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20now%20estimated%20to%20account%20for%20about%20half%20of%20the%20US%20homeless%20population%2C%20up%20from%20about%2010%25%20three%20decades%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20all%20boomers%20have%20benefited%20from%20the%20spike%20in%20housing%20prices%20and%20home%20equity.%20Wealth%20among%20boomers%20is%20very%20unevenly%20distributed%2C%20including%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20housing.%20Older%20renters%20and%20homeowners%20of%20color%20tend%20to%20have%20much%20higher%20housing%20costs.%20Molinsky's%20report%20found%20older%20Black%20homeowners%20had%20less%20than%20half%20the%20home%20equity%20of%20older%20white%20homeowners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMolinsky%20said%20the%20shortage%20of%20homes%20appropriate%20for%20aging%20would%20hurt%20lower-%20and%20middle-income%20boomers%20and%20boomers%20of%20color%20the%20hardest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%2