20Dragon.%20Growing%20up%2C%20he%20says%20he%20was%20his%20aunts'%20and%20uncles'%20favorite%20%E2%80%94%20and%20he%20knows%20why.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20was%20young%2C%20every%20Chinese%20New%20Year%2C%20my%20relatives%20would%20ask%2C%20'What%20zodiac%20is%20your%20child%3F'%20And%20my%20parents%20would%20say%2C%20'Oh%2C%20he's%20a%20dragon%2C'%26quot%3B%20said%20Koh%2C%20a%2023-year-old%20student%20at%20Singapore's%20Nanyang%20Technological%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20then%20all%20the%20relatives%20were%2C%20like%2C%20'Wow!%20He's%20going%20to%20grow%20up%20to%20be%20very%20rich%20and%20very%20successful%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BObviously%2C%20listening%20to%20all%20this%20every%20year%2C%20it'll%20build%20up%20your%20ego.%20You%20just%20think%2C%20'Oh%2C%20I'm%20a%20dragon%2C%20I'm%20special%2C'%26quot%3B%20Koh%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2298def9ac-3166-494d-be31-db89c9dd7f3a%5C%22%3EWhy%20the%20Dragon%20Year%20is%20special%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%2012%20Chinese%20zodiac%20animals%2C%20arranged%20in%20the%20following%20order%3A%20rat%2C%20ox%2C%20tiger%2C%20rabbit%2C%20dragon%2C%20snake%2C%20horse%2C%20goat%2C%20monkey%2C%20rooster%2C%20dog%2C%20and%20pig.%20The%20cycle%20repeats%20every%2012%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20lunar%20calendar%2C%202024%20is%20the%20year%20of%20the%20dragon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20dragon%20is%20the%20only%20mythical%20creature%20among%20the%20dozen%20animals.%20It's%20considered%20the%20most%20auspicious%20zodiac%20by%20the%20Chinese%20%E2%80%94%20and%20people%20in%20Asia%20make%20it%20a%20point%20to%20procreate%2C%20with%20hopes%20of%20birthing%20a%20child%20in%20those%2012%20calendar%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225591%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dancers%20and%20citizens%20wearing%20different%20costumes%20attend%20the%20Chinese%20New%20Year%20parade%20as%20part%20of%20the%20celebrations%20of%20Chinese%20New%20Year%20in%20New%20York%20City.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F674576739f2901eb6036d8a0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224233%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E2024%20is%20the%20year%20of%20the%20dragon%2C%20the%20only%20mythological%20creature%20in%20the%20Chinese%20zodiac.%3Cp%3EFatih%20Aktas%2FAnadolu%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Singapore's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftablebuilder.singstat.gov.sg%2Ftable%2FTS%2FM810091%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDepartment%20of%20Statistics%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20births%20went%20from%2036%2C178%20in%202011%20to%2038%2C641%20in%202012%2C%20the%20most%20recent%20dragon%20year.%20The%20number%20of%20births%20in%20the%20following%20year%2C%202013%2C%20dipped%20back%20down%20to%2035%2C681.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20similar%20trend%20of%20dragon-year%20birth%20spikes%20was%20observed%20in%201988%20and%202000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20born%20in%20the%20dragon%20year%20are%20said%20to%20be%20natural%20leaders%2C%20intelligent%2C%20and%20charismatic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDragon%20babies%20are%2C%20for%20the%20most%20part%2C%20intensely%20desired%20and%20prized%20by%20their%20parents.%20Culturally%2C%20dragons%20are%20held%20in%20the%20highest%20esteem%20%E2%80%94%20they%20were%20symbols%20of%20the%20emperor%2C%26quot%3B%20Ee%20Cheng%20Ong%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20economics%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eat%20the%20National%20University%20of%20Singapore%20(NUS)%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b9dde447-24db-4c28-8e50-ae6a77417a4c%5C%22%3ESpecial%20attention%2C%20but%20more%20competition%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20dragon%20babies%20in%20Singapore%20told%20Business%20Insider%20they%20were%20a%20source%20of%20pride%20for%20their%20family%20elders%2C%20who%20showered%20them%20with%20more%20attention%20because%20of%20their%20birth%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMelissa%20Anne%20Lim%2C%20a%20self-employed%2023-year-old%2C%20said%20that%2C%20like%20Jackson%20Koh%2C%20she%20was%20doted%20on%20growing%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20grandma%20loves%20that%20I'm%20a%20dragon%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Lim.%20%26quot%3BBeing%20a%20dragon%20baby%20kind%20of%20gave%20me%20a%20little%20more%20special%20attention%2C%20from%20the%20aunties%20especially.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDragon%20babies%20are%20also%20likely%20to%20face%20more%20competition%20in%20school%20and%20in%20the%20workplace%20from%20their%20direct%20peers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBecause%20schools%20have%20limited%20resources%2C%20including%20numbers%20of%20classrooms%2C%20facilities%2C%20and%20teachers%2C%20it%20is%20indeed%20correct%20that%20people%20born%20in%20such%20years%20may%20face%20disadvantages%20in%20terms%20of%20having%20larger%20class%20sizes%20and%20more%20competition%20in%20accessing%20'top%20schools%2C'%26quot%3B%20said%20Kelvin%20Seah%2C%20a%20senior%20economics%20lecturer%20at%20NUS.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20it's%20not%20just%20schools.%20Seah%20said%20dragon%20babies%20will%20also%20have%20a%20tougher%20time%20looking%20for%20jobs%20after%20graduation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20only%20so%20many%20jobs%20available%20in%20the%20economy.%20The%20larger%20cohort%20size%20means%20more%20competition%20for%20the%20limited%20number%20of%20jobs%20after%20graduation%2C%26quot%3B%20Seah%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20researchers%20from%20NUS%20published%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpapers.ssrn.com%2Fsol3%2Fpapers.cfm%3Fabstract_id%3D3032575%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%20on%20the%20life%20outcomes%20of%20dragon%20babies%20in%20Singapore%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20%E2%80%94%20which%20had%20a%20sample%20size%20of%204%2C608%20and%20is%20based%20on%20local%20birth%2C%20employment%2C%20and%20university%20admissions%20data%20from%201960%20to%202015%20in%20Singapore%20%E2%80%94%20found%20that%20Chinese%20dragon%20babies%20earned%206.3%25%20less%20than%20other%20Chinese%20birth%20cohorts%20upon%20entering%20the%20workforce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20also%20found%20that%20Chinese%20dragon%20babies%20were%202.3%25%20less%20likely%20to%20gain%20admission%20to%20local%20universities%20in%20Singapore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2202330f99-5e3e-4dba-adc8-c9d4f6cc7101%5C%22%3EA%20numbers%20game%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20places%20where%20the%20lunar%20year%20is%20observed%20%E2%80%94%20and%20accorded%20cultural%20significance%20%E2%80%94%20people%20born%20in%20the%20year%20of%20the%20dragon%20also%20face%20a%20unique%20set%20of%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20China%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20dragon%20babies%20taking%20the%20gaokao%2C%20the%20country's%20marathon%20university%20entrance%20exams%2C%20may%20face%20more%20intense%20competition%20with%20a%20larger%20cohort%2C%20said%20Stuart%20Gietel-Basten%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20social%20science%20and%20public%20policy%20at%20the%20Hong%20Kong%20University%20of%20Science%20and%20Technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Senior%20three%20students%20at%20New%20Century%20Senior%20High%20School%20are%20reviewing%20in%20a%20classroom%20in%20Qinhuangdao%20city%2C%20Hebei%20province%2C%20China%2C%20on%20the%20evening%20of%20June%203%2C%202024.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6745797b9f2901eb6036d8b6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223328%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEvery%20year%2C%20batches%20of%20Chinese%20high%20school%20students%20study%20intensely%20for%20the%20gaokao%2C%20an%20examination%20that%20will%20define%20their%20future.%3Cp%3ECFOTO%2FFuture%20Publishing%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EChina%20also%20sees%20birth%20rate%20spikes%20in%20dragon%20years.%20According%20to%20the%20National%20Bureau%20of%20Statistics%20of%20China%2C%20in%202012%2C%20China's%20birth%20rate%20reached%2014.57%20births%20per%201%2C000%20people.%20That%20was%20an%20increase%20from%2013.27%20births%20per%201%2C000%20people%20in%202011.%20Births%20dipped%20the%20following%20year%2C%20to%2013.03%20births%20per%201%2C000%20people%20in%202013.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20latest%20crop%20of%20dragon%20babies%20may%20have%20it%20easier%2C%20with%20competition%20evening%20out%20as%20birth%20rates%20drop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20cultural%20expectations%20may%20be%20changing%2C%20Gietel-Basten%20added.%20Dragon%20babies%20might%20have%20once%20been%20subject%20to%20great%20pressure%20to%20exceed%20expectations%2C%20but%20Gietel-Basten%20says%20he'd%20be%20%26quot%3Bsurprised%26quot%3B%20if%20that%20same%20level%20of%20pressure%20would%20be%20applied%20to%202024's%20dragon%20babies%20as%20they%20grow%20older.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20could%20even%20say%20that%20if%20you're%20a%20dragon%20baby%2C%20you%20become%20more%20confident%2C%26quot%3B%20Gietel-Basten%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20you%20could%20prosper%20not%20out%20of%20the%20pressure%20that's%20been%20put%20on%20you%2C%20but%20because%20of%20that%20confidence.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2299acf94b-a446-413c-9c3c-0aa33cec4aaf%5C%22%3EDragon%20baby%20spikes%20aside%2C%20birth%20rates%20remain%20low%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20it's%20hard%20to%20be%20a%20dragon%20baby%20or%20not%2C%20one%20thing%20is%20clear%3A%20Asian%20countries%20%E2%80%94%20including%20Singapore%20and%20China%2C%20both%20of%20which%20follow%20the%20lunar%20year%20%E2%80%94%20are%20facing%20a%20birth%20rate%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20China's%20population%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchinas-birth-rate-problem-wont-go-away-with-financial-incentives-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efell%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20second%20year%20in%20a%20row%20due%20to%20record-low%20birth%20rates.%20Singapore%20recorded%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.singstat.gov.sg%2F-%2Fmedia%2Ffiles%2Fpublications%2Fpopulation%2Fssn124-pg1-6.ashx